parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion and failure of brake lines can cause sudden brake failure, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: Brake pedal travels to the floorboard
brake pedal has little or no back pressure
sudden loss of brakes
front and rear brake lines crumbling with rust
brake lines separated due to corrosion.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

brake pedal does not return to its normal position
sudden loss of brakes
cruise control malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive wear of brake pads and rotors can cause vibration, noise, and poor braking performance, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: Noisy brakes

excessive brake pad wear
